dataIdInfo.idAbs: This is a set of the streams assessed by MPCA's surface water quality assessment process for the 2020 303(d)/305(b) integrated report to EPA. These streams are a subset of the 1:24,000 scale National Hydrography Dataset (NHD). This dataset includes impaired streams which may or may not yet have a TMDL plan approved by the US EPA as well as streams that support their designated uses, and those that had insufficient information to render a support judgment.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: These data are intended to be used for planning, informational, and cartographic purposes related to surface water quality in Minnesota.

themeKeys.keyword: inlandWaters, surface water, water chemistry, water quality

report.measDesc: These data have been audited to ensure every waterbody included in the 305(b) submission to EPA has a corresponding feature in this dataset, and that the use judgments are consistent between this spatial dataset and the assessment database as of the publication date.

These data contain a feature for every stream in the 305(b) inventory of assessed waters. High-resolution NHD is the primary dataset from which these features are drawn. If no feature exists in the NHD, MPCA staff will digitize a feature.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

overview.eaover:
AUID: The Assessment Unit Identifier - a unique identifier for each water unit in the assessment system.
NAME: Name of the feature associated with the AUID.
LOC_DESC: The beginning and end points of the beach in NAD 83 Decimal Degrees.
USE_CLASS: Use class per MN statute 7050.0470.
WATER_SIZE: The length of the reach in miles, according to the National Hydrography Dataset.
AQR: Aquatic Recreation Assessment FS: Fully Supporting aquatic recreation use. IF: Insufficient Information for an assessment. NS: Not Supporting aquatic recreation use. None: Has not been assessed for aquatic recreation use.
AQR_CAT: The consolidated assessment and listing methodology (CALM) category for the Aquatic Recreation use class.
AQR_LAST_A(Y): The most recent year the waterbody was assessed for Aquatic Recreation use.
AQC: Aquatic Consumption Assessment. IF: Insufficient Information for an assessment. NS: Not Supporting aquatic consumption use. None: Has not been assessed for aquatic consumption use.
AQC_CAT: The CALM category for the Aquatic Consumption use class.
AQC_LAST_A(Y): The most recent year the waterbody was assessed for Aquatic Consumption use.
AQL: Aquatic Life Assessment FS: Fully Supporting aquatic life use. IF: Insufficient Information for an assessment. NS: Not Supporting aquatic life use. None: Has not been assessed for aquatic life use.
AQL_CAT: The CALM category for the Aquatic Life use class.
AQL_LAST_A(Y): The most recent year the waterbody was assessed for Aquatic Life use.
DW: Drinking Water Assessment FS: Fully Supporting drinking water use. IF: Insufficient Information for an assessment. NS: Not Supporting drinking water use. None: Has not been assessed for aquatic consumption use.
DW_CAT: The CALM category for the Drinking Water use class.
DW_LAST_A(Y): The most recent year the waterbody was assessed for Drinking Water use.
LRV: Limited Resource Value (Class 7) Assessment FS: Fully Supporting limited resource value use. IF: Insufficient Information for an assessment. NS: Not Supporting limited resource value use. No: Has not been assessed for limited resource value use.
LRV_CAT: The CALM category for the Limited Resource Value (Class 7) use class.
Possible CALM category values include: 2: Waterbody’s assessed designated uses are fully supported, the designated use is fully supported, or parameter meets standards. 3: Data insufficient or inconclusive to assess. 4A: Impaired and a TMDL study has been approved by USEPA. 4B: Impaired but a TMDL study is not required because water quality standards are expected to be met in the near future. 4C: Impaired but a TMDL study is not required because the impairment is not caused by a pollutant. 4D: Impaired or threatened but does not require a TMDL because impairment is solely a result of natural sources. 4E: Impaired but existing data strongly suggests a TMDL study is not required because impairment is not caused by a pollutant or is due to natural conditions with only insignificant anthropogenic influence; a final determination of Category 4C or 4D will be made in the next assessment cycle pending confirmation from additional information. 5: Impaired and TMDL study has not been approved by USEPA.
None: Has not been assessed for the designated use. Not a CALM category.
HUC_8: The code of the 8 digit watershed that the feature is primarily associated with.
